Durban - As part of the inner city regeneration programme that is being driven by the eThekwini municipality, a multistorey Durban CBD building had sections of its upper floors closed on Tuesday. 
Municipal officials inspected the building, which is located at the corner of Monty Naicker and Yusuf Dadoo streets, and found several issues of non-compliance, including workers sleeping inside their working areas, a multitude of fire hazards and construction infractions.









